# Project Overview
FitTrack: Comprehensive Workout Tracking Application:
Project Overview
FitTrack is an Android application designed to help workout enthusiast track and monitor their workout progress. The app will provide a recording feature both strength training and cardio exercises.
Use Cases
-	Record and track workout progress, including exercise intensity and repetitions for consistent training
-	Get personalized workout suggestions and guidance for daily routines
Core Feature
-	Strength Training Library: Offer a pre-defined list of exercises for each body part
-	Cardio Exercise Library: Offer a pre-defined list of cardio workouts
-	Exercise Logging: Provide an input form for recording workout details, accessible by tapping each exercise
-	History Visualization: View workout progress through time-series graphs
-	Workout Summary: Display weekly and monthly workout frequency with exercise counts by category
Challenging Features with Higher Complexity
The following features involve higher implementation complexity and may not be completable within the semester timeframe. However, they are crucial for improving the overall application quality:
-	User Authentication: Implementation of secure login system using commercial Identity Provider (IDP)
-	Cloud Storage: Data management and storage solution using MongoDB Atlas
-	Smart Recommendations: "Workout of the Day" suggestions powered by cloud backend services

